AMEDA workflow: an introducing tutorial¶

This notebook will show you how to use AMEDA (1) on AVISO dataset and also help you to produce some figures of one specific day.

  • I. Create tools and directories
  • II. Get AVISO netcdf
  • III. Run AMEDA
  • IV. Produce some plot
  • V. Export tracks as netcdf

    • NB: The notebook need python and matlab to work properly

    (1) Le Vu, B., Stegner, A. and Arzouse, T. Angular Momentum Eddy Detection and tracking Algorithm (AMEDA) and its application to coastal eddy formation. To be submitted to Journal of Atmospheric and Ocean Technology.

    I. Create tools and directories¶

    Define directories to run the tutorial as homedir

    In [4]:
    homedir = '/home/blevu/Tuto/'

workdir = homedir+'AMEDA/'

    II. Get data netcdf¶

    Choose the date you want to analyse and write it in a file

    In [5]:
    date='20161025'

import datetime as dt
t1 = dt.datetime.strptime(date,'%Y%m%d')
dt=t1-dt.datetime(t1.year-1,12,31)

f=open(datadir+'date.txt','w+')
f.write(date + '\n')
f.close()

f=open(datadir+'date_jj.txt','w+')
f.write(str(dt.days) + '\n')
f.close()

        col=(.1,.1,.9); # anticyclone

        wid='-'; # largest eddy
    else:
        wid='--'; # true eddy
    mw.plot(x1,y1,ls=wid,color=col,lw=2)
